    <stitle>BRAKE COMPONENTS: This Service Manual Section should be used for reference only. For more current service
        information on all components go to the Bendix website from the ISIS Suppliers menu and refer to the Service
        Data Sheets. - MODULAR CONTROL VALVE (MV-3) - REMOVE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="0">
        <title>REMOVE</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply parking brake and block vehicle wheels.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Completely bleed air system.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove instrument panel access cover to expose valve body cover plate.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Mark or identify all air lines connected to valve. Then disconnect air lines.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove valve assembly from instrument panel.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove all fittings from the rear of the valve. Note the direction of all fittings.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
